  "subject": "Revert global-jjb to v0.92.7",
  "commit_message": "Revert global-jjb to v0.92.7\n\nv0.92.8 introduces an issue with some mvn jobs. This was change was\nmade due to a reported bug, and fixed the job in question, but seems\nto have a greater negative impact on other jobs. Because it is a\nrelease blocker, we will roll back for now, and then update once a\nmore universal fix is in place.\n\nChange-Id: Ie20cba8a30e95fec7d17643fffb419e31f2601b0\nIssue-ID: CIMAN-33\nSigned-off-by: Eric Ball <eball@linuxfoundation.org>\n",
